pull_request.title: Refactor liboqs-python classes / API changes
pull_request.body:
As per the weekly meeting, here is a PR for discussion of the code changes pushed yesterday.

The tasks & discussion points include:
* Update Py method names to match C KEM & Sig structs?
  - What about a common OO API for all the wrappers?
* Douglas: does the OQS_[KEM|SIG] represent an instance of an alg, or a general mechanism?
* Douglas: methods, secret_key as member vs method arg
* Douglas: include length checks in some of the functions
* Douglas: do KAT tests somewhere?
* Wrapper doesn't support nist-branch Sig interface at present
* Should vars in the 'details' dict be moved into the class, and then replace 'details' with a Py getter property?
* Ben: defer when the SO is loaded for testing?
  - _load_shared_obj() is called during import, which sets up the liboqs var. Loading liboqs is coupled to import time, which is a bit problematic
  - can't monkeypatch _load_shared_obj() until after the wrapper has been imported
  - some parts of the code can't be tested due to the above, unless there's refactoring

pull_request.title: Add setup.py install script
pull_request.body:
Added setup.py installer to give users the opportunity to install into local virtual dev environments & for later hosting on PyPI. Used setup.py format suggestions from:

* https://docs.python-guide.org/writing/structure/
* https://github.com/kennethreitz/samplemod

Fixed some errors in the README too.

pull_request.title: Add build scripts and continuous integration for ARM
pull_request.body:
Adds
- `scripts/arm-cross-compile.sh` which cross-compiles an ARM binary from Ubuntu Linux, assuming an appropriate toolchain is installed.
- `scripts/arm-run-tests-qemu.sh` which tests ARM binaries on Ubuntu Linux using QEMU.

Fixes #444. 

Note there are currently some bugs; separate issues have been created to track these.
- Picnic doesn't compile. (#461)
- Autoconf configuration a little quirky.  (#462)
- Segmentation faults when qTESLA runs. (#463)
